PART 5 — Configure the Asterisk dialplan
14. Open your extensions.conf:
bashsudo nano /etc/asterisk/extensions.conf

15. Add this sub-context (anywhere in the file, e.g. at the bottom):
[sub-record]
exten => s,1,NoOp(Recording call ${UNIQUEID})
 same => n,Set(RECFILE=/var/spool/asterisk/recordings/${STRFTIME(${EPOCH},,%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S)}_${CALLERID(num)}.wav)
 same => n,MixMonitor(${RECFILE})
 same => n,Return()

16. In the context where your calls are handled (e.g. [internal-routing]), add two things:
First, call the recording sub at the start of each call:
same => n,GoSub(sub-record,s,1)
Second, add a hangup handler that triggers transcription when the call ends:
exten => h,1,NoOp(Hangup — transcribing ${RECFILE})
 same => n,System(/var/lib/asterisk/agi-bin/transcribe_agi.py ${RECFILE} &)

Note: The h extension must be in the same context where the call actually ends
(where Dial() lives), not inside sub-record.

Save and exit: Ctrl+O → Enter → Ctrl+X

17. Reload the dialplan:
bashsudo asterisk -rx "dialplan reload"

18. Verify the dialplan loaded correctly:
bashsudo asterisk -rx "dialplan show sub-record"
Should show your sub-record context with the MixMonitor line.

